  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Using Social Accountability tools to eliminate corrupt practices in DAs</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Activities Under Objective One are:
1.Conduct Rapid assessment in four District Assemblies
2.Stakeholders engagement and consultation meeting 
3.Formation and Election of Social Accountability Groups for Anti Corruption Campaigns 
4.Training of Citizens on  Social Accountability  Forum (SAF)
5.Organizing Social Accountability fora (SAF) to build capacity of citizens and promote transparency and good governance at the DAs. 
6.To facilitate Learning events in 4DAs and share with partners  

Activities Under Objective Two are:
1.Collaborate with DAs to organize town hall meetings twice per year
2.Conduct radio talk-shows to support government decentralization policy issues at the local level 
3.Conduct monitoring in all implementing district to track the use of public resources.
4.Tracking of revenue mobilization and is utilization.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of monitoring pan is to provide road map for the implementation of all project activities. The team will resort to use the institutional framework to track result, reports and project performance. Project activities would take place at the district and community level and would be reported through well trained field officers using well structured reporting format at all levels in the project implementation cycle. 

The various partner organizations will collaborate and work with their respective stakeholders such as DAs officials and citizens groups in fighting against corruption. The output indicator will measure immediate/short term results. The achievement of this short term results will contribute to the objectives and the goals. Under this project output indicators will be measured for performance &#x201C;20 percent of revenue mobilisation increased in the four (4) DAs 50 percent of citizens show interest and confidence in participating in the assembly meetings.</narrative>
  </description>
